ESPTOOL
=======

Installation of esptool
-----------------------
  - sudo apt install esptool

Prerequisites to flashing
-------------------------
  - make the user member of the dialout group: sudo usermod -a -G dialout uwe

Example on how to use esptool
-----------------------------
  - ~/bin/esptool/esptool --chip auto -p /dev/ttyUSB0 write-flash 0x0 l9lorry01g-firmware.factory.bin

whereas ...
 - ~/bin/esptool/esptool is the location of the tool (to be fine tuned)
 - /dev/ttyUSB0 is the USB port to be used. See script docker_image_esphome_dashboard_lcl_start.sh 
    for detecting the USB port in question or here:
      USB_TO_TEST="/dev/ttyUSB0 /dev/ttyACM0"
      ADDITIONAL_USB=""

      for USB in ${USB_TO_TEST}; do
        if [ -e ${USB} ]; then
          ADDITIONAL_USB="${ADDITIONAL_USB} --device=${USB}"
        fi
      done
 - l9lorry01g-firmware.factory.bin is the downloaded firmware binary from the end of the install process
